<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="427" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1712,2027]" lastBlockId="26.[151,1437,153,467]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="427" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1892,1919]" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daniel" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[328,507,1893,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="slovenica">
<emphasis box="[328,507,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Spiris slovenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[847,948,1893,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis box="[847,948,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">S. striata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on external characters of the imagines, and the genitalia have to be investigated. In the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daniel" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[840,975,1929,1955]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="slovenica">
<emphasis box="[840,975,1929,1955]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">S. slovenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which have been studied, the cucullus is bent ventrad, and in particular, the large ventral thorn on the tip of the cucullus is strongly bent, forming a hook; clavus trapezoidal, with ventral margin entirely straight, dorsal margin parallel to ventral margin for half-length of clavus, in apical half evenly tapered towards the rounded, spiny tip (but see Remarks below). As in 
<taxonomicName box="[1262,1363,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis box="[1262,1363,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">S. striata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, some melanic forms are known.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="427" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,153,467]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,590,224,251]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
Description. Imago (
<figureCitation box="[445,577,224,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–28" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1663,1688]" captionTargetBox="[237,1353,224,1596]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[227,1360,219,1599]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 19–28. 19. S. striata, male, Paterna del Madera, Albacete, (Spain) (coll. RMV); 20. S. striata, female, El Cerro, Gredilla la Polera, Burgos, (Spain) (coll. RMV); 21. S striata f. melanoptera, male, Loma del Rey, Quintanilla Sobresierra, Burgos, (Spain) (coll. RMV); 22. El Cerro, Gredilla la Polera, Burgos, (Spain) (coll. RMV); 23. S. slovenica, male, Crni Kal, Petrinje, (Slovenia) (coll. RMV); 24. S. slovenica, female, Crni Kal, Petrinje, (Slovenia) (coll. RMV); 25. S. Slovenica f. melanoptera, male, Goriski Kras, Kostanjevica, (Slovenia) (coll. RMV); 26. S. Slovenica f. melanoptera, female, Goriski Kras, Kostanjevica, (Slovenia) (coll. RMV); 27. L. bifasciata, male, Val d´Ese, Corse, (France) (coll. RMV); 28. L. bifasciata, female, Costa Smeralda, Sardinia, (Italy) (coll. RMV)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246054/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Figs 23–26</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Average wingspan 
<quantity box="[814,915,224,251]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.54" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" unit="mm" value="35.4">35.4 mm</quantity>
(n = 10; 
<quantity box="[1022,1148,225,251]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" unit="mm" value="35.0" valueMax="42.0" valueMin="28.0">28–42 mm</quantity>
). Wing maculation as described for the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,153,467]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,421,296,323]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[324,408,296,323]" captionStart="FIGURE 38" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1277,1302]" captionTargetBox="[156,1431,529,1213]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[148,1439,517,1223]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 38. S. slovenica, male and female genitalia, gen. prep. 5821JG m. Crni Kal, Petrinje, (Slovenia), 5820JG f. Crni Kal, Petrinje, (Slovenia)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246066/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Male genitalia with short uncus, base with several long simple setae, central part somewhat constricted, tip blunt and broad; tegumen and vinculum broad, rounded semi-circular; juxta large oval, with a central longitudinal strip of weaker sclerotisation; valvae elongate rectangular, strongly sclerotized, apically bent ventrad, ventral apical thorn bent ventrad to form a short hook, dorsal base of valva with prominent dorsally directed trapezoid clavus. Female genitalia as for the genus.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246066/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" startId="26.[151,250,1277,1302]" targetBox="[156,1431,529,1213]" targetPageId="26">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1277,1338]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,288,1277,1302]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">FIGURE 38.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daniel" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[294,415,1278,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="slovenica">
<emphasis box="[294,415,1278,1302]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">S. slovenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male and female genitalia, gen. prep. 5821JG m. Crni Kal, Petrinje, (Slovenia), 5820JG f. Crni Kal, Petrinje, (Slovenia).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1384,2023]" box="[199,550,1384,1411]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,406,1384,1410]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Immature stages.</emphasis>
Not studied.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1384,2023]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,389,1420,1446]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Molecular data.</emphasis>
The publicly available DNA Barcode data of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daniel" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[911,1045,1420,1447]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="slovenica">
<emphasis box="[911,1045,1420,1447]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">S. slovenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
allow the inclusion of this species in our phylogenetic analysis. Intraspecific uncorrected p-distances are 0–1.51%, with a mean of 1.05% (n = 6). The nearest interspecific p-distance is 3.89% to 
<taxonomicName box="[648,750,1493,1519]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis box="[648,750,1493,1519]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">S. striata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Staudinger" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[766,960,1492,1519]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bipunctata">
<emphasis box="[766,960,1492,1519]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Spiris bipunctata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a p-distance of 4.10–4.75% to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daniel" baseAuthorityYear="1939" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="slovenica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">S. slovenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the Barcode of Life Database (BOLD), 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daniel" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[717,851,1528,1555]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="slovenica">
<emphasis box="[717,851,1528,1555]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">S. slovenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by BIN AAL9555. Sequence data on the nuclear wingless gene are not available.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1384,2023]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
In the phylogenetic results, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daniel" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[510,644,1600,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="slovenica">
<emphasis box="[510,644,1600,1627]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">S. slovenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is strongly supported as monophyletic (1.00 PP, 100% BS) and poorly supported as sister (59% BS, PP&lt;0.90) to 
<taxonomicName box="[622,723,1637,1663]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Coscinia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="striata">
<emphasis box="[622,723,1637,1663]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">S. striata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[738,823,1636,1663]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1865,1890]" captionTargetBox="[206,1235,194,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[196,1250,194,1752]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 62. Phylogenetic tree (General Time Reversible model + Gamma distribution) obtained from Bayesian analysis of combined COI Barcode and wingless gene data of the Arctiinae specimens studied; numbers above branches are Posterior Probabilities ≥ 0.90, numbers below branches are Bootstrap values obtained from 1,000 Bootstrap replicates of a Maximum Likelihood analysis conducted with RaxML. Within the C. cribraria clade, the subspecies C. c. benderi, C. c. rippertii and C. c. ibicenca are marked in slightly darker green. The black vertical bars on the right mark BOLD BINs; the specimens of BIN ACE7017 are nested within BIN AAD9042. The scale bar (upper left) represents substitutions per nucleotide position." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246102/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="427" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1384,2023]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1671,1698]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Biology.</emphasis>
Univoltine, flying from June to July, showing preference for xerothermic steppe areas; diurnal. Larvae are polyphagous on a wide variety of plant species (
<bibRefCitation author="Witt, T. J. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[732,972,1708,1734]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" refId="ref27927" refString="Witt, T. J. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2011) Noctuidae Europaea. Lymantrinae and Arctiinae including Phylogeny and Check List of the Quadrifid Noctuoidea of Europe, 13. Entomological Press, Soro, 448 pp." type="book" year="2011">Witt &amp; Ronkay 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="427" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1384,2023]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,463,1743,1770]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
Distribution (
<figureCitation box="[363,450,1743,1770]" captionStart="FIGURE 60" captionStartId="39.[151,250,1094,1119]" captionTargetBox="[235,1356,214,1043]" captionTargetId="figure@39.[227,1360,211,1047]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 60. Distribution map of S. slovenica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3246098/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Witt, T. J. &amp; Ronkay, L." box="[630,892,1744,1770]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" refId="ref27927" refString="Witt, T. J. &amp; Ronkay, L. (2011) Noctuidae Europaea. Lymantrinae and Arctiinae including Phylogeny and Check List of the Quadrifid Noctuoidea of Europe, 13. Entomological Press, Soro, 448 pp." type="book" year="2011">Witt &amp; Ronkay (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Daniel" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[906,1042,1744,1771]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="slovenica">
<emphasis box="[906,1042,1744,1771]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">S. slovenica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the Julian Alps and the north-western mountainous area of 
<collectingCountry box="[597,695,1780,1806]" name="Slovenia" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Slovenia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[752,838,1780,1806]" name="Croatia" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Croatia</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Huemer, P." box="[850,1023,1780,1807]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" pagination="225 - 231" refId="ref24612" refString="Huemer, P. (2012) Der Slowenische Grasbar (Spiris slovenica) - eine Neuentdeckung fur Osterreich (Lepidoptera, Erebidae: Arctiinae). Wissenschaftliches Jahrbuch der Tiroler Landesmuseen, 5, 225 - 231." type="journal article" year="2012">Huemer (2012)</bibRefCitation>
indicates that the actual distribution range might be much wider, and he gives confirmed records from southern 
<collectingRegion box="[990,1094,1816,1842]" country="Austria" name="Karnten" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Carinthia</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1109,1197,1816,1843]" name="Austria" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Austria</collectingCountry>
), and from the Italian regions of Trentino-Alto Adige to Friuli-Venezia Giulia, as well as from Lazio and Apulia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="427" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1384,2023]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1888,1914]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Remarks.</emphasis>
In 
<collectingCountry box="[351,403,1888,1914]" name="Italy" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Italy</collectingCountry>
, there seems to be an extraordinary variability in the genitalic morphology between different populations. The dissection of some scattered specimens gives astonishing results as if in 
<collectingCountry box="[1140,1191,1924,1950]" name="Italy" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Italy</collectingCountry>
would exist up to five completely different sympatric species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[624,689,1961,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[624,689,1961,1987]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Spiris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Alberto Zilli, pers. comm.). The authors, after the dissection of a great number of Iberian and French 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[555,620,1997,2023]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Spiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[555,620,1997,2023]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Spiris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, have been unable to find the existence of the same genitalic variability.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
